::{{DIcon|Talk}} The people of Okhema seem to fear you.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504017117-->
:::'''Castorice:''' They cannot be blamed for this. I am the "mortician" in the holy city. I was also once... the holy maiden who oversaw warfare in Aidonia. In their eyes, I am no more than a walking envoy of death.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I would like to hear your story.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504017119-->
::::'''Castorice:''' I have no memories of the time before I came to Aidonia. From what I'm told, I was merely a drifter who wandered the wastelands until Aidonia took me in.
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504017121-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504017121-->
::::'''Castorice:''' Aidonia is a city that worships Thanatos. Its residents regard death as their destined end... Unlike the Kremnoans longing to die in battle, the Aidonians see death as the blessed final destination for life.
::::'''Castorice:''' However, that does not mean that Aidonians do not treasure life. On the contrary, they believe that it is only by living a long life and tempering oneself will one gain a soul tenacious enough to cross the River of Souls and meet Thanatos.
::::'''Castorice:''' The Aidonian found me in the wilds. They strongly believed that I had received the blessing of the Death Titan, that my hands could spare them from the River of Souls and send them straight to the great Thanatos.
::::'''Castorice:''' So, I was revered as the "Maiden of War"... Only I could grant the deceased Aidonian warriors the comfort and respect that they deserve.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I'd like to hear stories about Aidonia.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504017121-->
